        <h2 id="what-is">What is NeuronWriter?</h2>
        <p>NeuronWriter is a SERP-driven content optimization platform headquartered in Poland and operated by the team behind ContentSuccess. It entered the market as a budget alternative to Surfer SEO and Clearscope. The pitch: real-time content scoring backed by NLP analysis of the top-ranking pages for your keyword, starting at $23/month instead of $119–$129/month.</p>

        <p>The core product does five things:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Content Editor</strong> — a writing surface that scores your draft in real time against the SERP</li>
          <li><strong>Competitor analysis</strong> — pulls headings, terms, and structure from the top 10 results</li>
          <li><strong>NLP term suggestions</strong> — recommended entities and phrases to include for topical coverage</li>
          <li><strong>AI Writer</strong> — paragraph-level generation against your outline</li>
          <li><strong>Internal linking suggestions</strong> — surface link opportunities across your indexed content</li>
        </ol>

        <p>What NeuronWriter is <em>not</em>: a research suite, a publishing platform, or a content workflow. It scores what you write. Producing and publishing the content is on you.</p>

        <h2 id="features">NeuronWriter features — the full 2026 walkthrough</h2>
        <p>The surface is narrower than Surfer or Frase, but the core scoring engine is competitive. Here is what actually matters in daily use.</p>

        <h3>1. Content Editor — the scoring core</h3>
        <p>Enter a target keyword, pick a region/language, and NeuronWriter pulls the top 10 results, extracts terms, and gives you a target Content Score (0–100). As you write or paste, the score updates with a list of suggested terms to add, current word count vs target, and a heading-structure recommendation. Functionally similar to Surfer's editor; visually less polished.</p>

        <h3>2. Competitor analysis</h3>
        <p>One-click view of competitors' H1/H2/H3 structures, word counts, term coverage, and meta tags. Useful for outline building. The export to brief is rougher than Frase's brief module but covers the essentials.</p>

        <h3>3. AI Writer</h3>
        <p>Paragraph and section generation against your outline. Quality is acceptable for first drafts; needs human editing on every section. Character limits are tied to your plan (15K on Bronze, 100K on Platinum), and high-volume teams will hit those caps fast.</p>

        <h3>4. Internal linking</h3>
        <p>Index your site, then NeuronWriter suggests internal links per article from your existing pages. Saves time, but the matching is keyword-only — no semantic context, so suggestions sometimes miss the obvious.</p>

        <h3>5. AppSumo lifetime deals (historical)</h3>
        <p>NeuronWriter previously sold lifetime access through AppSumo. Those deals are no longer active, but if you find a stack on a resale forum, factor reliability and support response time into the math — lifetime-deal users report slower help.</p>

        <h2 id="pricing">NeuronWriter pricing — what it really costs in 2026</h2>
        <p>NeuronWriter is transparent about sticker price. We'll show sticker plus the execution cost most reviews skip.</p>

        <div class="table-wrap">
